        <abstract> 
<p>CD is pleased by BP’s appreciative opinion of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>. He never intended to claim that he originated the doctrine that species have not been independently created. The only novelty in his work is the attempt to explain <hi rend="italic">how</hi> species became modified and how the theory of descent explains large classes of facts. If he has taken anything from BP, he has done so unconsciously. Gives names of those he would have mentioned in any account of authors who maintained that species have not been separately created.</p>  
<p>CD greatly admires BP’s <hi rend="italic">Philosophy of creation</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
